  "prompt": "How can I get rid of little bumps on my face?",
  "response": "There are several ways to address bumps on your face, depending on their cause:\n\n1. For acne bumps:\n- Use salicylic acid or benzoyl peroxide treatments\n- Keep your face clean\n- Use non-comedogenic moisturizers\n- Avoid touching your face\n- Consider over-the-counter acne products\n\n2. For skin texture issues:\n- Exfoliate regularly (chemical or physical)\n- Use retinol or retinoid creams\n- Try chemical peels\n- Maintain a consistent skincare routine\n\n3. For milia (small white bumps):\n- Gentle exfoliation\n- Use products with salicylic acid\n- Professional extraction by a dermatologist\n\n4. For allergic reactions or irritation:\n- Identify and avoid triggers\n- Use gentle, fragrance-free skincare products\n- Apply hydrocortisone cream\n\n5. General skincare tips:\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Get enough sleep\n- Manage stress\n- Use sunscreen\n\nIf bumps persist or are concerning, consult a dermatologist for personalized advice and treatment.",
